<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Register an Animal</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1003" relname="condition">If you have some sort of disability ,</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="span">you may want or need a support animal</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="3" relname="purpose">to help you in your day-to-day life .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1005" relname="span">The 2 main types of support animals are service animals and emotional support animals .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1006" relname="span">These different types of support animal are subject to different laws and certification requirements .</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="1008" relname="preparation">However ,</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="9" relname="circumstance">once you know what this necessary certification is ,</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1008" relname="span">getting the right paperwork for your animal is a breeze .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1010" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="preparation">Qualifying for a Support Animal</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="span">Determine what type of support animal</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="12" relname="elaboration">you need .</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1014" relname="span">Service dogs are individually trained</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="14" relname="purpose">to perform critical daily functions for people with physical or psychiatric disabilities .</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="span">Emotional support animals</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="16" relname="elaboration">( ESA ) , on the other hand , are not trained ,</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1018" relname="span">but instead offer support for individuals</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="elaboration">suffering from psychiatric or emotional disabilities .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="span">Most individuals with service dogs suffer from a severe disability , such as blindness or asthma ,</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="20" relname="elaboration">that makes it very difficult to perform major life tasks .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1023" relname="span">These dogs are then trained</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="22" relname="purpose">to help the individual perform that major life task</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1023" relname="elaboration">( e.g. , helping a person with limited sight get around in public ) .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1027" relname="span">The Americans with Disabilities Act</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="25" relname="restatement">( ADA )</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1026" relname="same_unit">defines “ disability ” very broadly ,</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1028" relname="same_unit">so do n't feel</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1029" relname="span">like yours is n't a “ real ” disability</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="29" relname="cause">just because it 's not as bad as someone else 's .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1031" relname="span">Anything</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="elaboration">that makes a normal function of life difficult qualifies as a disability .</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1033" relname="preparation">Have a doctor formally diagnose your disability .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1035" relname="concession">Although this is n't required by law ,</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1035" relname="span">a doctor will be able to tell you</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="35" relname="elaboration">whether obtaining or training a service dog is the best thing for you .</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="38" relname="condition">If you do n't already have a dog ,</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1037" relname="span">the doctor may also be able to refer you to a reputable provider of properly trained service animals .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="40" relname="attribution">Note</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1040" relname="span">that you 're not required to obtain a service dog from a professional training program .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1041" relname="span">You can also train your own service dog yourself ,</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="41" relname="condition">if you feel up to the task .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1042" relname="joint">Be prescribed an emotional support animal for any mental health issues .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1045" relname="contrast">ESAs are not covered by the ADA ,</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">but they are still protected by other laws</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="45" relname="elaboration">that prevent discrimination against disabled individuals .</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="48" relname="purpose">In order for your animal to be covered , though ,</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1050" relname="span">it needs to have been formally prescribed to you by a mental health professional .</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1051" relname="span">This prescription can be in the form of a formally written letter from your therapist or counselor ,</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="49" relname="elaboration">stating that the presence of your ESA is necessary for your mental or emotional health .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1052" relname="span">The Fair Housing Act</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1054" relname="attribution">( FHA ) says</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1054" relname="contrast">that landlords cannot bar your ESA from living with you ,</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1054" relname="contrast">while the Department of Transportation also requires airlines to allow passengers with mental and emotional disabilities to fly with their ESAs .</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1056" relname="span">Make sure your animal is well-behaved enough</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="55" relname="purpose">to be a support animal .</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1059" relname="span">Apart from the particular training</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="57" relname="elaboration">that service dogs are required to have ,</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1058" relname="same_unit">the only other behavioral requirement for support animals is that they not behave inappropriately in public .</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1061" relname="span">This can include behaving aggressively ,</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1062" relname="span">biting or scratching other dogs or people ,</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1063" relname="contrast">toileting inappropriately ,</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="contrast">or otherwise disrupting business .</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1066" relname="condition">If your support animal is not well behaved ,</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1066" relname="span">businesses can then legally bar you and your animal from entering the premises ,</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="65" relname="cause">since the animal constitutes a “ direct threat ” or “ fundamental alteration ” to their business .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="span">Train your dog to do a vital function ,</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="67" relname="condition">if you want it to be a service dog .</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1070" relname="preparation">Remember , service dogs must be able to do a specific task ,</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="joint">not just provide emotional support .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1073" relname="condition">If you already own a dog ,</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1074" relname="span">teach it</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="72" relname="purpose">to help you perform a major life task</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1074" relname="purpose">in order to have it qualify as a service dog .</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1075" relname="span">This task can be something as simple</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1076" relname="span">as helping you cross the street</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1077" relname="joint">if you have limited vision</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1078" relname="span">or barking for assistance</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="78" relname="circumstance">when you have trouble breathing .</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="81" relname="preparation">Note that this type of training can be very time-consuming ,</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1080" relname="span">sometimes taking several years .</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1083" relname="condition">If your disability is particularly urgent ,</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1083" relname="span">you may be better off just buying a dog</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="83" relname="elaboration">that has already been trained .</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="1042" relname="joint">Getting the Right Paperwork</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="1042" relname="joint">Get certification for your ESA from a mental health professional .</segment>
<segment id="87" parent="1087" relname="preparation">Have your therapist , counselor , or psychiatrist write you a formal letter</segment>
<segment id="88" parent="1089" relname="attribution">stating</segment>
<segment id="89" parent="1089" relname="joint">that you have a mental or emotional disability</segment>
<segment id="90" parent="1089" relname="joint">and that having your ESA is necessary for your mental health .</segment>
<segment id="91" parent="1092" relname="condition">If possible ,</segment>
<segment id="92" parent="1092" relname="span">have your doctor write this letter on a professional letterhead</segment>
<segment id="93" parent="92" relname="purpose">to give it an added layer of legitimacy .</segment>
<segment id="94" parent="1095" relname="contrast">If you do n't have a formal therapist ,</segment>
<segment id="95" parent="1095" relname="contrast">or your therapist is unwilling to write you a letter ,</segment>
<segment id="96" parent="1096" relname="span">you may be able to use an online mental health service</segment>
<segment id="97" parent="96" relname="purpose">to acquire this type of letter .</segment>
<segment id="98" parent="1098" relname="span">However , be very careful</segment>
<segment id="99" parent="100" relname="circumstance">when using this type of service ,</segment>
<segment id="100" parent="1099" relname="span">since many of these types of websites may be scams .</segment>
<segment id="101" parent="1102" relname="span">Carry this letter with you</segment>
<segment id="102" parent="101" relname="purpose">so you can use it as documentation for an ESA .</segment>
<segment id="103" parent="1103" relname="span">You 'll need to provide this letter to a landlord or airline employee</segment>
<segment id="104" parent="103" relname="elaboration">who asks to see your ESA 's certification .</segment>
<segment id="105" parent="1107" relname="preparation">Just to be safe ,</segment>
<segment id="106" parent="1107" relname="span">keep a scanned copy of this letter in your home</segment>
<segment id="107" parent="106" relname="circumstance">while carrying the other copy with you at all times .</segment>
<segment id="108" parent="1109" relname="span">Note that this is the only documentation</segment>
<segment id="109" parent="108" relname="elaboration">the law requires ESAs to have .</segment>
<segment id="110" parent="1111" relname="span">Avoid paying a website</segment>
<segment id="111" parent="110" relname="purpose">to “ register ” your support animal .</segment>
<segment id="112" parent="1113" relname="span">Apart from having a formal letter from a mental health professional ,</segment>
<segment id="113" parent="112" relname="result">support animals are not required by law to be certified or registered to any database .</segment>
<segment id="114" parent="1116" relname="span">Websites</segment>
<segment id="115" parent="114" relname="elaboration">that try to sell this type of certification</segment>
<segment id="116" parent="1117" relname="span">are usually trying to sell to people</segment>
<segment id="117" parent="116" relname="elaboration">who do n't actually know the law ,</segment>
<segment id="118" parent="1115" relname="purpose">so just steer clear of them .</segment>
<segment id="119" parent="1119" relname="span">Oftentimes , people will pay</segment>
<segment id="120" parent="1120" relname="same_unit">to “ register ” their pets as support animals</segment>
<segment id="121" parent="122" relname="attribution">because they think</segment>
<segment id="122" parent="1122" relname="span">it 's required</segment>
<segment id="123" parent="124" relname="attribution">or they think</segment>
<segment id="124" parent="1123" relname="span">it makes their support animal look more official .</segment>
<segment id="125" parent="1126" relname="span">In reality , anyone</segment>
<segment id="126" parent="125" relname="elaboration">who understands the law</segment>
<segment id="127" parent="1128" relname="attribution">will probably think</segment>
<segment id="128" parent="1128" relname="span">the person</segment>
<segment id="129" parent="128" relname="elaboration">using this type of certification does n't actually qualify for a support animal .</segment>
<segment id="130" parent="131" relname="attribution">Be aware</segment>
<segment id="131" parent="1130" relname="span">that you do n't need to show documentation for a service dog .</segment>
<segment id="132" parent="1104" relname="joint">According to the ADA , business owners and employees are not allowed to demand documentation for your service dog .</segment>
<segment id="133" parent="1133" relname="span">Instead , they 're only allowed to ask</segment>
<segment id="134" parent="1134" relname="joint">if the animal is required because of a disability</segment>
<segment id="135" parent="1135" relname="span">and what task the animal has been trained</segment>
<segment id="136" parent="135" relname="purpose">to do .</segment>
<segment id="137" parent="1136" relname="contrast">Owners and employees are also not allowed to demand that the dog demonstrate its task</segment>
<segment id="138" parent="1136" relname="contrast">or ask about the nature of your disability .</segment>
